Commentary: Hasan aims full and straight first ball, Ronchi chipping it uppishly but, ultimately, safely into the leg side
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: Ronchi leaps down the track this time to turn the ball into a half volley, muscling his shot through midwicket to get off the mark with a boundary
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Ronchi, FOUR runs

Commentary: Hasan's change-up is a bouncer, Ronchi ducking underneath it
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: in the air, and safe! Ronchi sets himself for a big hit down the ground, but gets a terrible connection. Fortunately for him, Pollard is a little slow getting in from deep mid on
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Ronchi, 1 run

Commentary: slugged into the leg side, and he's off the mark with a single
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run

Commentary: Hasan aims for a surprise yorker, but the ball slips out as a low full toss. No harm done, though, as Ronchi's drive goes straight to mid on
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: Gul hits a length, Farhan tapping him softly into the leg side
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Sahibzada Farhan, no run

Commentary: good line and length, with a touch of wobble outside off, and this time it's worked into the covers
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Sahibzada Farhan, no run

Commentary: swatted across the line by Farhan, and the ball rolls along the turf to Pollard at deep mid on
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run

Commentary: huge swish outside off from Ronchi, but he's beaten on the outside edge, the ball swinging away after passing the bat
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: Sameen misses his length slightlly and Ronchi is quick to hop onto the back foot, pulling well in front of square for a brace
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Ronchi, 2 runs

Commentary: a touch of nip back in off the track, and Ronchi punches to cover point off the back foot
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: tip-and-run single from Farhan, tapping a full ball to cover and setting off
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run

Commentary: clubbed over midwicket! Ronchi was camped on the back foot, waiting for a short one, and Hasan's length was a little too short
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Ronchi, SIX runs

Commentary: a touch quicker from Hasan, but fuller too and Ronchi is struck on the thigh pad
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Ronchi, 1 leg bye

Commentary: wicket to wicket stuff from Hasan again, and it's worked to midwicket
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Sahibzada Farhan, no run

Commentary: worked off the straight, no single to be had though
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Sahibzada Farhan, no run

Commentary: short again from Hasan, and Farhan rocks back into a one-legged pull, but he can't beat the man at short fine
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run

Commentary: Farhan slices under his drive a little, but manages to get it up and over the infield and away for a couple
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Sahibzada Farhan, 2 runs

Commentary: Umaid's finds his pad, but there's space for a single
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 leg bye

Commentary: short and rising towards Ronchi's midriff, and the ball is pulled out into the deep
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Ronchi, 1 run

Commentary: picked up over midwicket by Farhan, but he can't find the gap on the leg side boundary
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run

Commentary: such a clean strike! Ronchi's second of the innings, and the 100th six of the tournament. Once again he uses his feet to attack the ball, swatting a length delivery up and over cover
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Ronchi, SIX runs

Commentary: Umaid tests him with another short one, Ronchi rolling his wrists over his pull to keep it down and collect one to the man at deep square
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Ronchi, 1 run

Commentary: appeal for lbw as Sameen slides one in full and fast, but the umpire says no and it may well have been going down the leg side. No review taken
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Ronchi, 1 leg bye

Commentary: chance! But it's a very tough one. Farhan drove a full one hard back at the bowler, who got half a hand to it, and that was all reflex. Even the umpire took evasive action
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run

Commentary: picks out the man in the deep! Ronchi was looking to get after the bowling, but he hits a length delivery almost straight out to Dawson at deep midwicket. The umpires just ask to have another look for the no-ball, and it's very tight. Eventually they decide he's got something behind the line, so the dismissal stands
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Ronchi, OUT
Dismissal_text: L Ronchi c Dawson b Sameen Gul 21 (15b 1x4 2x6) SR: 140.00

Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Bell, no run

Commentary: slipping down the leg side, but Bell can't get bat to it, the ball kissing the pad and rolling through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Bell, no run

Commentary: full, and Bell comes forward to drive to mid off, pinching a quick single to get off the mark
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: deft touch! This is Bell's strength. He just stands at the crease and presses off the back foot, but times - and places - it so well that the ball scoots past the point fielder and away for four
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, FOUR runs

Commentary: on a length, outside off, and Bell decides to let this one go
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, no run

Commentary: this time he puts bat to ball on a wide delivery outside off, chopping it down to third man for one
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: pushed forcefully into the covers, but straight at the fielder
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Sahibzada Farhan, no run

Commentary: short and fast from Riaz, but Farhan is deep in his crease and waiting for it. He pulls the ball high in the air towards midwicket, the ball landing safely in no-man's land between the two fielders out there
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Sahibzada Farhan, 2 runs

Commentary: play and a miss, Riaz beating a driving Farhan's outside edge
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Sahibzada Farhan, no run

Commentary: Sameen bends his back on this full one, delivering it at 140km/h, and it's placed down the ground for a quick single
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: edged! Farhan skips out and swings, the ball kissing the outside edge and flying down to the third man boundary
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Sahibzada Farhan, FOUR runs

Commentary: Farhan clears his front leg and hacks at a length delivery, sending the ball bouncing down the ground where Pollard hauls it in at long on
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run

Commentary: Bell takes his bottom hand off this pull shot, but manages to place it into a gap and grab a single
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: spliced into the air, and the Dawson/Sameen combo works for a second time! Farhan tried to pull a short-ish delivery into the stands, but the ball rushed on to him and took the splice, rocketing up into the night sky as Dawson charged in from the rope, diving forward to hold the catch. Once again, they have a look at Sameen's back heel and a potential no ball, but once again he's just behind the line
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Sahibzada Farhan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Sahibzada Farhan c Dawson b Sameen Gul 15 (18b 1x4 0x6) SR: 83.33

Commentary: short and rising from a middle stump line, Bell collecting a single with a controlled pull to midwicket
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: Pollard trundles in and floats one down full and straight, Bell working the ball to the fielder at midwicket
Commentary_short: Pollard to Bell, no run

Commentary: wider this time, and Bell cuts out to the cover sweeper
Commentary_short: Pollard to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: Talat waits to dab a length ball to third man, but he bottom edges the effort and it goes nowhere
Commentary_short: Pollard to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: so much for Talat, who sees a slow bouncer from Pollard outside off and tries to cut down on it, succeeding only in sending an edge through to Akmal, who makes no mistake
Commentary_short: Pollard to Hussain Talat, OUT
Dismissal_text: Hussain Talat c †Kamran Akmal b Pollard 0 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: there's nothing on these medium pace deliveries from Pollard, but he finds just enough bounce to trouble the batsmen and he beats Delport's outside edge first ball
Commentary_short: Pollard to Delport, no run

Commentary: chopped out through gully, and that raises the team fifty
Commentary_short: Pollard to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: looped up, and Delport slaps it hard back at Dawson, who lets it through for a single
Commentary_short: Dawson to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: precious little flight on this one, or turn, but it's aimed right at the stumps and Bell can't get it away
Commentary_short: Dawson to Bell, no run

Commentary: fuller this time, and Bell comes forward to drive to cover, where the fielder fumbles to prompt (brief) thoughts of a quick single
Commentary_short: Dawson to Bell, no run

Commentary: beaten on the cut! Bell backs away and tries to manufacture something, but the ball zips past him
Commentary_short: Dawson to Bell, no run

Commentary: this time he does lay bat on the cut, but finds the point fielder
Commentary_short: Dawson to Bell, no run

Commentary: timing from Bell! He really didn't seem to have hit this very well, but he placed it just well enough to beat a diving point fielder and timed it just well enough to beat a sprinting cover sweeper on the rope
Commentary_short: Dawson to Bell, FOUR runs

Commentary: slow offcutter from Pollard, and it's muscled down to long off
Commentary_short: Pollard to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: another canny change of pace from Pollard, who holds this one back and gets Bell to play - and miss - his cut too early
Commentary_short: Pollard to Bell, no run

Commentary: swatted out into the deep on the leg side, a diving Dawson saving two runs at the boundary's edge
Commentary_short: Pollard to Bell, 2 runs

Commentary: flicked off the pads and down to fine leg
Commentary_short: Pollard to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: Delport uses his bottom hand to rifle a swipe out to wide long on, and the fielder has some work to do to cut that one off as well
Commentary_short: Pollard to Delport, 2 runs

Commentary: straight back down the ground! It was the length that was key, too full, and Delport just swung through the line to lift it back over Pollard's head
Commentary_short: Pollard to Delport, SIX runs

Commentary: Umaid targets the pads, and Bell flicks across them to collect a single
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: a touch on the short side, and Delport pulls but Umaid has cover in the deep to keep them to one
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: short again, and this time it's Bell on the pull out to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: big swing from Delport, but the ball comes of the cue end and dribbles to long on
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: stifled appeal from Umaid as he hits Bell's pad, but it's clearly headed down leg and quickly quashed
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Bell, 1 leg bye

Commentary: another meaty strike from Delport as he eyes up a full length delivery, but he doesn't get under it and long on keeps them to one
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: and he sticks to the short-pitched line of attack, Delport pulling well in front of square to midwicket
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: Bell clears his left leg and sets himself to scythe a cut away, but he can't quite beat the field and the only result is a quick single
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: in the air, and safe! The thing that saved Delport here was the complete lack of timing, a short ball rocketing up at him and taking the splice of his pull shot, but landing safely
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: Bell uses the predictable short length now, waiting deep in the crease and ramping another short ball up and over the keeper. Some athletic fielding down at third man saves two runs
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, 2 runs

Commentary: cut over point! Bell spots width, and doesn't bother keeping this one down
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, FOUR runs

Commentary: almost chipped back to the bowler! Riaz comes around the wicket, and the ball takes the leading edge of Bell's nudge to leg, popping up in the air. But it hits the ground before Riaz can get to it, and the pair share a smile and a friendly word at the end of the over. No, really
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, no run

Commentary: full, wide and very slow from Pollard. Delport waits on the ball, and then clunks a drive down to long off
Commentary_short: Pollard to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: Bell fakes a back-away to leg, and then nurdles a single into the leg side when he doesn't get the line or length he wants
Commentary_short: Pollard to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: round the wicket comes Pollard, digging the ball in very short. Delport pulls down to long on
Commentary_short: Pollard to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: chopped out through cover for one
Commentary_short: Pollard to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: Delport swings hard into a drive, but he can only get the ball as far as long off
Commentary_short: Pollard to Delport, 1 run

Commentary: flicked into the leg side, just the one
Commentary_short: Pollard to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: chipped in the air, inside out over cover, but the timing wasn't quite there so it's just two. Again, the ball is short - that's been Peshawar's main mode of attack tonight
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Bell, 2 runs

Commentary: Bell sends a back of a length delivery down the ground with an uncharacteristically ungainly hack
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Bell, 2 runs

Commentary: this time he backs away and angles the blade to find a single to third man
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: whoops, this one slips out as a wide
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Delport, 1 wide

Commentary: down the track, back over the bowler! They've not given Delport the length he wants, so he makes it himself by getting down the pitch and he times the stroke superbly too
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Delport, SIX runs

Commentary: great comeback from the bowler, sending down a yorker that zips right under the bat outside off
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Delport, no run

Commentary: edged, and four! Lucky strike for Delport, who threw his hands into a drive and edged the ball down to third man
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Delport, FOUR runs

Commentary: Hasan comes back, and his first ball seams in off the track, Bell flicking out through square leg for one
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: Hasan strikes! The bowlers have kept them quiet with a short-pitched attack, but this one was full and straight, with a bit of cut on it, and delivered from around the wicket. Delport made room, but the cut and the length took the ball past the bat and onto the stumps
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Delport, OUT
Dismissal_text: CS Delport  b Hasan Ali 29 (18b 1x4 2x6) SR: 161.11

Commentary: Hasan greets him with a first ball yorker, and there's a quick single taken. Hasan charges around, picks the ball up and throws the stumps down with Asif Ali's foot still in the air ... but his bat grounded! Could have been a very interesting one, had his bat been in the air
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball from Hasan at 115km/h, it slips out as a low full toss and Bell drives for a single
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: Asif Ali doesn't need a sighter! Second ball, he climbs into a length delivery and smashes the ball up into the second tier of the stadium. Huge
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Asif Ali, SIX runs
Hasan Ali to Asif Ali, no run

Commentary: Bell backs away but can't time his backfoot thump, so it's just the one to cover
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: and another! Asif eyes up a full ball, outside off, and clubs it cleanly over long on for his second six of the evening
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Asif Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: and he falls in the pursuit of a third! The ball was full again, so the shot was on, but he just didn't time it as well as he would have liked, and can only get the ball as far as Riaz at long off
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Asif Ali, OUT
Dismissal_text: Asif Ali c Wahab Riaz b Sameen Gul 13 (5b 0x4 2x6) SR: 260.00

Commentary: Faheem laces a good-looking cut first ball, and they take a single as the point fielder stops it but then has a shy and misses
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Faheem Ashraf, 1 run

Commentary: the timing is good, the placement is even better. Bell backs away a touch and cuts in the air, beating point but not going so square that the cover sweeper can cut it off. And he's into the 40s
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Bell, FOUR runs

Commentary: through the leg side now! The ball was a touch on the short side, and Bell set himself deep in the crease to have a mow into the leg side, getting it out of the middle and beating long on's right
Commentary_short: Sameen Gul to Bell, FOUR runs

Commentary: chipped in the air into the open space in front of midwicket, just the one
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Faheem Ashraf, 1 run

Commentary: short, pulled, and it goes in the air but lands safely in front of midwicket. Bell slips turning for the second, so it's only a single
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: it's short - again - and Faheem pulls hard and high, but only as far as the fielder at deep square leg
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Faheem Ashraf, OUT
Dismissal_text: Faheem Ashraf c Umar Amin b Umaid Asif 2 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 66.66

Commentary: short again, and this one possibly just held up a little in the pitch. Whatever the case, Bell is much too early into his pull, and misses
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Bell, no run

Commentary: pushed down the leg side, and he'll have to bowl that one again
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Bell, 1 wide

Commentary: full this time, the surprise yorker. Bell overbalances and tumbles over keeping it out, but still has the presence of mind for a quick single
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Bell, 1 leg bye

Commentary: too short, too wide, and it's another one in the extras column
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Shadab Khan, 1 wide

Commentary: very full, and it's dug out down the ground
Commentary_short: Umaid Asif to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: Riaz comes around the wicket, delivering the ball full and straight at the stumps. Well kept out
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: just short of a diving third man fielder! Bell ramped the slower ball bouncer, but it was too slow to get the ball going and Sameen was almost in business, running in from third man
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, 2 runs

Commentary: caught off a no ball! It was on a length but quite wide. Bell held nothing back on the cut, but he sent it straight out to the deep point fielder. He was trudging off, but the umpires held him back, and Riaz has nothing behind the line. Instead of a wicket, it's a no ball and the next one's a Free Hit
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, 1 no ball

Commentary: clubbed down the ground, Pollard puts in some yards to cut it off at long on, but they're back for a second
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Shadab Khan, 2 runs

Commentary: sliced down to third man, where Sameen runs around and cuts it off
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Shadab Khan, 2 runs

Commentary: will this one count? Yes it will! A fired up Riaz runs in and hurls down a yorker at 146km/h, it's too quick for Shadab and the stumps are shattered
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Shadab Khan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Shadab Khan  b Wahab Riaz 6 (5b 0x4 0x6) SR: 120.00

Commentary: another attempted yorker from Riaz, but Samit gets some bat on it to get the ball to third man
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Patel, 1 run

Commentary: full toss from Hasan, and Samit just needs to chip it up and over the infield to get four
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Patel, FOUR runs

Commentary: and the stumps take another bashing! Offcutter from Hasan, and Samit aims an awful hoick at it, swinging past the ball and turning to see his stumps in disarray
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Patel, OUT
Dismissal_text: SR Patel  b Hasan Ali 5 (3b 1x4 0x6) SR: 166.66

Commentary: surprise bouncer from Hasan, and Sami gloves it to gully to get it off the mark
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Mohammad Sami, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball, Bell spots it and works a single behind square on the off side to bring up the 150
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Bell, 1 run

Commentary: almost chipped back to him! Sami plays too early, but the ball lands in front of the bowler
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Mohammad Sami, no run

Commentary: shorter this time, and the ball hits Sami in the belly and they pinch a single
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Mohammad Sami, 1 leg bye

Commentary: through him! Riaz sends down a quick yorker, and it beats Sami for pace - but it's outside off
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Mohammad Sami, no run

Commentary: full again, this time Sami gets bat on ball to turn the strike over to Bell
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Mohammad Sami, 1 run

Commentary: there's the fifty! And he brings it up in exemplary style with a beautiful touch, backing away and ramping an uppercut over the keeper's head and away for four
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, FOUR runs

Commentary: big swish outside off, but this one is through him in a flash
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, no run

Commentary: another fiery yorker, Bell gets bat on it to tap the ball to point, and takes on Andre Fletcher's arm from deep point for a risky second run to keep the strike. He's not quick enough, and he's got to go
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Bell, 1 run, OUT
Dismissal_text: IR Bell run out (sub [Fletcher]/†Kamran Akmal) 54 (46b 6x4 0x6) SR: 117.39

Commentary: the final ball is another quick yorker that hits the no. 11 on the pad. Riaz appeals, but the umpire says no. They ask for a review. Replays show there's no bat on it, it hits the back leg, but the all is missing the leg stump, according to the ball tracker. That looked closer live, but I guess it's not out
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Muhammad Musa, 1 leg bye

Commentary: tapped to point, and they're up and running straight away
Commentary_short: Patel to Kamran Akmal, 1 run

Commentary: landing straight and spinning down the leg side, but Imam's glance goes to square leg
Commentary_short: Patel to Imam-ul-Haq, no run

Commentary: this time he makes room to open up the off side, placing a backfoot punch through the cover field to open his account
Commentary_short: Patel to Imam-ul-Haq, FOUR runs

Commentary: misfield, four more! Imam came down the track and pinged a drive out of the middle, Asif Ali is slow getting down to it and the ball goes right through him at cover
Commentary_short: Patel to Imam-ul-Haq, FOUR runs

Commentary: flicked with the spin into the leg side
Commentary_short: Patel to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: tapped down to long off, Kamran keeps the strike and 11 come from the first over
Commentary_short: Patel to Kamran Akmal, 1 run

Commentary: on a length and nicely straight, Kamran tapping it back to the bowler. His dad's in the crowd watching tonight
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Kamran Akmal, no run

Commentary: Kamran stands on tip-toe to ride the bounce, but he bottom edges his backfoot punch and it goes nowhere
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Kamran Akmal, no run

Commentary: Sami attacks the stumps, Kamran drives watchfully to mid off
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Kamran Akmal, no run

Commentary: rising off a length at 144km/h, Kamran hopping across and nudging off his hip for one
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Kamran Akmal, 1 run

Commentary: a short ball at 136km/h, and it's top edged! Imam tried to pull, but it rushed on to him and took a top edge, coming to ground in front of the third man fielder
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: laced over point! Short and wide, and Kamran Akmal loves them there. He doesn't bother keeping the shot down, and times it superbly
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Kamran Akmal, FOUR runs

Commentary: his first ball is nicely accurate, and Imam is half forward to defend it
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Imam-ul-Haq, no run

Commentary: Musa hits a good length again, and at a good pace, 142km/h. Imam tucks defensively to leg
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Imam-ul-Haq, no run

Commentary: bristling bouncer! It was only 135km/h, but Imam ducked quickly to get underneath it
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Imam-ul-Haq, no run

Commentary: beaten on the outside edge! Imam flashes outside off, but misses a 141km/h delivery
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Imam-ul-Haq, no run

Commentary: now he puts bat to ball, pulling powerfully into the leg side, where Faheem gets a hand to it to take the sting out of the shot and save the boundary
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: and now he's got a wicket too! Kamran Akmal's eyes light up at a short, wide one but he cuts in the air and straight into the hands of the point fielder
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Kamran Akmal, OUT
Dismissal_text: Kamran Akmal c sub (PD Salt) b Muhammad Musa 7 (8b 1x4 0x6) SR: 87.50

Commentary: a missed chance! Imam was forward and drove in the air back to the bowler, who just couldn't get down quick enough in his follow through, and the ball pops out
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: sliced down to third man to get off the mark
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Malan, 1 run

Commentary: flicked off the pads, but straight to short fine
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Imam-ul-Haq, no run

Commentary: a late dab brings another single to third man
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: a slightly flat-footed push from Malan, and he's beaten on the outside edge
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Malan, no run

Commentary: another little fiddle outside off, another play-and-miss
Commentary_short: Mohammad Sami to Malan, no run

Commentary: pace from Musa at 143km/h, but Imam uses his feet, getting down the track and slapping a drive over cover
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Imam-ul-Haq, FOUR runs

Commentary: Musa adjusts his length, bowling this one a little shorter, and Imam flicks a single off the hip
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: Musa hustles Malan with a full one, the ball squirting off the outer half of the bat and going to point
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Malan, no run

Commentary: bouncer! Musa hurtles to the crease, gets nicely side on, and then slams in a bouncer halfway down to get Malan ducking
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Malan, no run

Commentary: a second wicket for the teenager! This is a slightly fortunate one. The ball was quick, but it was on leg stump and Malan could have had runs, had he hit it a yard either side of the fielder. Instead, he tapped it straight to him, Samit holding a simple catch
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Malan, OUT
Dismissal_text: DJ Malan c Patel b Muhammad Musa 1 (6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 16.66

Commentary: chipped uppishly! This rose off a leg stump line once again, and Amin was a little rushed in his attempted glance, but the ball - if it hit any bat - goes to ground between the short fine fielder and the wicketkeeper
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Umar Amin, no run

The umpires want to have another look at the replay, but that just serves to confirm Riaz' demise
